  "description" : "[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/InkWarrior/Universal-Wardrobe/refs/heads/main/workshopimages/I-Iron%20Frame%20Update.png[/img]\nWelcome to the 2.0! This update is rather smaller, yet it’s sort of inaugural for the future updates to come. For now, these are the highlights of the update:\n[list]\n[*] 47 new individual clothing items, most of them made by [b]Tea-Loving Lad[/b]\n[*] New aspect for the Customization table and it’s dyes.\n[/list]\nI guess that’s it, now go and play!\n\n[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/InkWarrior/Universal-Wardrobe/refs/heads/main/workshopimages/II-Introduction.png[/img]\nDon’t you feel that sometimes the appearance of npcs gets a bit, uhm, stale? Wouldn’t you like to see the vanilla “wardrobe” to be a bit more variated and less generic? Well, say no more! [b]Universal Wardrobe[/b] was created with the intent of giving a bit more of spice to the npcs of the game by adding not only fully and original new outfits, but also a lot of variants for outfits of this mod and vanilla Starbound. \n\n[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/InkWarrior/Universal-Wardrobe/refs/heads/main/workshopimages/III-Content.png[/img]\n[list]\n[*] New crafting table: [b]Customization Desk[/b]. This table will give you access to a lot of variants and new items, such as unique clothing items and dyes.\n[*] 24 new Back items.\n[*] 164 new Head items, along with 100 new variants (vanilla and modded).\n[*] 50 new Chest items, along with 87 new variants (vanilla and modded).\n[*] 41 new Leg items, along with 12 new variants (vanilla and modded).\n[*] 55 brand new Costume Boxes.\n[*] 5 new codexes.\n[*] 48 new dyes.\n[/list]\n\n[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/InkWarrior/Universal-Wardrobe/refs/heads/main/workshopimages/IV-Mod%20Compatibility.png[/img]\nHey! here is a [url=https://steamcommunity.com/workshop/filedetails/discussion/3492414889/690868475627995537/]list[/url] with all the mods compatible with Universal Wardrobe. [b]Also, yes, this is compatible with Frackin Universe[/b]\nBesides the compatible mods, here are a couple of mods recommended to play alongside Universal Wardrobe: [b]Miniknog Rearmed[/b], [b]Historical Armor[/b] and its distribution patch, [b]Infinite Storage[/b] and [b]OpenStarbound[/b] (Which is not a mod, yet its new cosmetic slots allow for even more variated and unique outfits!).\n\n[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/InkWarrior/Universal-Wardrobe/refs/heads/main/workshopimages/V-Credits.png[/img]\n-[b] Armok [/b] : A big thanks to him for helping me refine the writing of the codexes and item descriptions, while also making helpful suggestions for the mod.\n-[b] Tea-Loving Lad [/b] : A big shoutout to him for helping me with a lot of colorful and frankly amazing clothing additions to the mod.\n-[b] Pixelflame [/b] : Shoutout to her too for contributing with the Scientist Skirt item.\n\n[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/InkWarrior/Universal-Wardrobe/refs/heads/main/workshopimages/VI-Whats%20Next.png[/img]\nAs I said, 2.0 is sort of an inaugural update. When I uploaded this mod, I said that next updates wouldn’t be on the scale of what was added in the release version, yet when I found myself planning the contents of the 2.0, I realized that I just did that! Instead, I decided to divide it into batches. I can at least talk of the next updates to some degree (this is subject to change):\n[list]\n[*] 0.2.1 – Focused on adding a couple of outfits for some of the base villagers in the game, and perhaps 2 or 3 new npcs.\n[*] 0.2.2 – Update focused mostly on Floran clothing stuff.\n[*] 0.2.3 – This updated is focused on expanding the space stuff. There are a couple of unique armors (actual armors) and small dungeons planned here.\n[/list]\n\nAs for other mods, I don’t like to talk much about stuff I have little to no progress, so this is the stuff I’m sure to be releasing eventually at least:\n[list]\n[*] Last update for [b]Gyrojets![/b] (besides hotfixes and stuff).\n[*] New update for the [b]Risk of Rain[/b] mod. New visuals and objects mostly.\n[*] [b]Project Parasprite[/b] mod. New stuff, new objects, new monsters, new dungeons and a lot of unique lore for this little part of the game.\n[*] [b]Protectorate[/b] mod. A lore expansion for the Protectorate, which is close to being released! New objects and decorations, outfits, npcs and a lot of new lore in form of codices.\n[/list]\nThat’s it for today!",
